Research 
My research interests are
 Fine-grained parallelism 
 Compiling for Multi-processor Systems 
 Distributed Systems 
I am also a member of the  Programming Languages Research Group  at the  Computer Science Dept.  at  Pitt  
Currently I am working on a project involving Instruction Scheduling
with Register constraints for Superscalar and VLIW machines. 
My advisors are  Dr. Mary Lou Soffa  and  Dr. Rajiv Gupta  